Introduce the two module-scope helpers that both `search()` and `searchWithRelations()` will call.

File: `packages/db/src/models/accommodation/accommodation.model.ts`

At the top of the file (after imports, import `sql` from `drizzle-orm`):
```ts
const NUMERIC_NULLABLE_FIELDS = new Set<string>([
    'averageRating', 'reviewsCount', 'minPrice', 'maxPrice'
]);

function buildSortExpr(column: AnyColumn, order: 'asc' | 'desc', field: string) {
    if (NUMERIC_NULLABLE_FIELDS.has(field)) {
        return order === 'desc'
            ? sql`${column} DESC NULLS LAST`
            : sql`${column} ASC NULLS LAST`;
    }
    return order === 'desc' ? desc(column) : asc(column);
}
```

These are module-private (no export).

Mirror the existing `sanitizeSortBy()` helper (line 46) but for the new `sorts[]` array.

```ts
function sanitizeSorts(sorts: SortField[] | undefined): SortField[] | undefined {
    if (!sorts) return undefined;
    const filtered = sorts.filter((s) => ALLOWED_SORT_FIELDS.has(s.field));
    return filtered.length > 0 ? filtered : undefined;
}
```

Reuse the existing `ALLOWED_SORT_FIELDS` set — do NOT fork it. Keep `sanitizeSortBy()` (preserve verbatim).

Import `SortField` type from `@repo/schemas`.

